 <div class="story">
   <p>We check our blog when we wake up and, to our surprise, Oprah saw ProblemChild on Twitter after our mom tweeted about it and 500,000 people entered their names into ProblemChild. We officially have 500,000 users.

   But we need to know who our users are. Okay. We just did this. Lets write a user variable for every user that signed-up for ProblemChild overnight.</p>
 </div>

 <div class="lesson">
   <span class="lesson-instructions">
